<i>Dear Ms. Ruan, I'm calling to inform you</i>

21
00:03:25,380 --> 00:03:29,839
<i>that by 5:00 p.m. on August 3, 2024,</i>

22
00:03:29,839 --> 00:03:33,966
<i>you hadn't submitted
a new novel outline to your editor.</i>

23
00:03:33,966 --> 00:03:39,760
<i>Since the completion
of your last novel, it's been...</i>

24
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:42,299
a full year already!

25
00:03:43,499 --> 00:03:46,540
<i>Got it, got it, Editor Shen.</i>

26
00:03:46,540 --> 00:03:50,139
Ms. Ruan is sorting out
her belongings at home.

27
00:03:50,139 --> 00:03:55,760
She remembered she promised
the outline by the end of this month.

28
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:59,280
Then, may I ask if she has
decided on the theme?

29
00:04:01,980 --> 00:04:03,420
Not yet.

30
00:04:03,420 --> 00:04:05,953
It's been a year, Ruan Yu!

31
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:09,740
You're a rising full-time web novelist.

32
00:04:09,740 --> 00:04:12,260
Do you want to become a has-been?

33
00:04:12,260 --> 00:04:14,700
But there's no inspiration, what can I do?

34
00:04:14,700 --> 00:04:18,580
<i>Because you're cooped up all day!</i>

35
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:23,439
<i>Inspiration isn't handed to you,</i>

36
00:04:23,439 --> 00:04:27,520
<i>it's built through hands-on experience, got it?</i>

37
00:04:27,520 --> 00:04:30,940
<i>May 11, Sunny.</i>

38
00:04:30,940 --> 00:04:33,879
<i>I encountered Xu Huai Song three times today.</i>

39
00:04:33,879 --> 00:04:38,099
<i>The first time was on my way to the office
with Chinese test papers.</i>

40
00:04:38,099 --> 00:04:43,060
<i>I saw him and some classmates
being punished in the hallway.</i>

41
00:04:43,060 --> 00:04:45,180
<i>The Dean looked angry.</i>

42
00:04:45,180 --> 00:04:47,300
I've got it.

43
00:04:47,300 --> 00:04:50,700
What? The theme?

44
00:04:50,700 --> 00:04:52,200
Yes.

45
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:57,490
Setting in a campus, theme, and secret crush.

46
00:04:57,490 --> 00:05:00,439
What do you think?
<i>[Jan. 1, 2014 | SOS! Today Xu Huai Song...]</i>

47
00:05:04,392 --> 00:05:08,140
<i>[2014 New Year's Eve]
[Su City No.1 High School]</i>

48
00:05:08,140 --> 00:05:12,900
<i>At midnight that day, for New Year's Eve fireworks,</i>

49
00:05:12,900 --> 00:05:16,460
<i>the playground was packed.</i>

50
00:05:16,460 --> 00:05:22,440
<i>All of high school, she had never been so close</i>

51
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:26,340
<i>to her secret crush.</i>

52
00:05:42,140 --> 00:05:48,539
<i>Eleven, ten, nine, eight, seven, six...</i>

53
00:05:48,539 --> 00:05:52,919
<i>-- As if unconsciously, she snuck to his left.
Five! Four! Three!</i>

54
00:05:52,919 --> 00:05:56,380
<i>Two! One!</i>

55
00:06:04,219 --> 00:06:08,420
<i>Unexpectedly, the moment the fireworks exploded,</i>

56
00:06:08,420 --> 00:06:11,020
<i>he suddenly took her hand.</i>

57
00:06:46,620 --> 00:06:49,684
<i>Sorry. I took the wrong hand.</i>

58
00:07:30,299 --> 00:07:32,700
<i>She turned around in shock,</i>

59
00:07:33,639 --> 00:07:36,666
<i>only to see in the flickering light...</i>

60
00:07:37,299 --> 00:07:40,380
<i>his apologetic look.</i>

61
00:07:42,520 --> 00:07:45,060
<i>He released her hand</i>

62
00:07:45,060 --> 00:07:47,040
<i>and said awkwardly,</i>

63
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:51,580
<i>"Sorry."</i>

64
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:54,480
<i>"I took the wrong hand."</i>

65
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:59,690
<i>[I Really Want to Whisper In Your Ear - Draft]</i>

66
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:21,470
<i>I took the wrong hand?</i>

67
00:08:22,140 --> 00:08:24,406
<i>I took the wrong hand.</i>

68
00:08:25,300 --> 00:08:27,779
<i>So whose hand is right?</i>

69
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:33,460
<i>Did Xu Huai Song like someone else?</i>

70
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:54,200
<i>You're not writing</i>

71
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:59,079
<i>an unrequited love based on him, are you?</i>

72
00:08:59,079 --> 00:09:00,340
<i>Come on!</i>

73
00:09:00,340 --> 00:09:03,679
<i>Life is hard enough.
Who goes online for a tragedy?</i>

74
00:09:03,679 --> 00:09:09,580
<i>Yes. The author has a hard life.</i>

75
00:09:09,580 --> 00:09:13,280
<i>The heroine should have a happier one.</i>

76
00:09:13,280 --> 00:09:15,580
<i>[I Really Want to Whisper In Your Ear - Draft]</i>

77
00:09:25,020 --> 00:09:28,579
<i>With this said, his heart pounded,</i>

78
00:09:28,579 --> 00:09:33,520
<i>louder than the fireworks overhead.</i>

79
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:36,020
<i>No one knew that</i>

80
00:09:36,020 --> 00:09:40,413
<i>"I took the wrong hand" was just a cover-up.</i>

81
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:16,440
<i>[Hang City]</i>

82
00:10:27,740 --> 00:10:30,672
For your review, Great Editor Shen.

83
00:10:35,900 --> 00:10:39,760
Your novel is going to be a hit.

84
00:10:42,779 --> 00:10:47,879
Personal experience is so touching, right?

85
00:10:50,100 --> 00:10:52,499
But, don't you worry that

86
00:10:52,499 --> 00:10:57,280
he might see this novel?

87
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:59,419
Of course I considered the risk.

88
00:10:59,419 --> 00:11:03,620
You know, it was my unrequited love.

89
00:11:03,624 --> 00:11:06,640
Back then, he didn't even know my name.

90
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:08,719
Even if he sees it, he won't know it's me.

91
00:11:08,719 --> 00:11:13,180
Besides, would unattainable flowers
like Xu Huai Song read romance novels?

92
00:11:13,180 --> 00:11:15,260
You can rest easy.

93
00:11:15,940 --> 00:11:17,664
Indeed.

94
00:11:24,292 --> 00:11:26,496
Hello, Mom. What's up?

95
00:11:27,260 --> 00:11:29,420
Okay.

96
00:11:29,420 --> 00:11:31,053
Bye-bye.

97
00:11:33,280 --> 00:11:36,656
Another blind date?

98
00:11:41,226 --> 00:11:45,940
Hey, your new ringtone...

99
00:11:45,940 --> 00:11:51,820
sounds like Xu Huai Song's tune
at the school anniversary, "After the Rain."

100
00:11:51,820 --> 00:11:53,380
Stop guessing.

101
00:11:53,380 --> 00:11:57,580
I only changed it to recall memories.

102
00:11:57,580 --> 00:12:01,880
Well, be careful. It might recall something else.

103
00:12:29,220 --> 00:12:31,980
I want an explanation!

104
00:12:31,980 --> 00:12:35,220
Do you understand?

105
00:12:35,220 --> 00:12:37,279
Listen, Ma'am. I'm sorry.

106
00:12:37,279 --> 00:12:39,820
- But this verdict isn't going to change.
- What's going on?

107
00:12:39,820 --> 00:12:42,500
- Her house was leased to American students.
- It's my house!

108
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:45,260
- But they neither paid nor moved out.
- Why should I give them money?

109
00:12:45,260 --> 00:12:47,819
So she went and cut off the water and power,

110
00:12:47,819 --> 00:12:50,579
and contacted Jay to file a lawsuit
to claim the rent.

111
00:12:50,579 --> 00:12:53,080
But she was charged with trespassing,

112
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:56,400
and required to pay a heavy fine instead.

113
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:58,940
- Now she's arguing with Jay.
- It was nice chatting with you but I have to go.

114
00:12:58,940 --> 00:13:01,659
- You can't go! Hey, you can't go!
- Ma'am.

115
00:13:01,659 --> 00:13:04,439
- It's not settled yet! You can't go!
- Let go of me! Let go! Ma'am.

116
00:13:04,439 --> 00:13:09,286
- You can't go!
- This is America. You have to obey the laws of the USA.

117
00:13:13,320 --> 00:13:16,300
It doesn't matter what country's laws
we are talking about.

118
00:13:16,300 --> 00:13:18,450
If you lose, you lose.

119
00:13:18,450 --> 00:13:20,510
Finally, a fellow countryman!

120
00:13:20,510 --> 00:13:23,180
Tell me, aren't they bullying me?

121
00:13:23,180 --> 00:13:26,240
Emotionally or rationally, I shouldn't pay them!

122
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:30,360
The court doesn't recognize
emotion or reason, only law.

123
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:33,799
So I have to compensate them?

124
00:13:33,799 --> 00:13:35,500
That's right.

125
00:13:37,660 --> 00:13:41,400
But I have two questions.
I want your honest reply.

126
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:45,540
First, what's the expiration date on the lease?

127
00:13:45,540 --> 00:13:48,500
And for which months are you claiming rent?

128
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:52,820
The lease expired in February.
They didn't renew the lease.

129
00:13:52,820 --> 00:13:54,980
We only made a verbal agreement.

130
00:13:54,980 --> 00:13:58,800
But they haven't paid since February.

131
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:02,220
After the lease expired,

132
00:14:02,220 --> 00:14:04,960
did you know they were still living in your house?

133
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:06,926
Yes, I did.

134
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:11,560
Are you sure you knew?

135
00:14:11,560 --> 00:14:13,341
In that case...

136
00:14:15,699 --> 00:14:18,260
I didn't know?

137
00:14:18,260 --> 00:14:22,499
If you didn't know, it's not only the unpaid rent,

138
00:14:22,499 --> 00:14:24,100
but also they were trespassing.

139
00:14:24,100 --> 00:14:29,319
After all, they occupied your property
without your knowledge.

140
00:14:29,319 --> 00:14:32,220
I don't need to say more, right?

141
00:14:32,220 --> 00:14:33,920
Thank you so much!

142
00:14:33,920 --> 00:14:36,959
I never knew such a solution existed!

143
00:14:36,959 --> 00:14:39,839
The law is rigid, but people are flexible.

144
00:14:39,839 --> 00:14:43,626
Song, are you sure that you want
to be meddling in my affairs?

145
00:14:43,626 --> 00:14:44,900
This is my case.

146
00:14:44,900 --> 00:14:48,530
I guess we have different definitions
of the word "meddle".

147
00:14:48,530 --> 00:14:52,180
And in my view, I'm cleaning up your mess.

148
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:56,720
Listen, just because you have
some type of big win rate

149
00:14:56,720 --> 00:14:59,533
doesn't mean you can be an arrogant prick.

150
00:15:02,900 --> 00:15:05,280
I'll take that as a compliment.

151
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:07,913
And just do your job.

152
00:15:13,260 --> 00:15:15,264
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

153
00:15:15,264 --> 00:15:19,280
Let's go to my office
where we can talk more privately and I can help you.

154
00:15:28,640 --> 00:15:32,419
Boss, you didn't notice, Jay was green with rage.

155
00:15:32,419 --> 00:15:35,075
He deserved it.

156
00:15:35,075 --> 00:15:37,460
I don't care about his rage.

157
00:15:37,460 --> 00:15:39,340
I care about the case.

158
00:15:39,340 --> 00:15:42,920
Otherwise, it's the firm's reputation at stake.

159
00:15:43,980 --> 00:15:47,179
Drink less cola. It's bad for you.

160
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:53,360
By the way, this is the criminal case
I mentioned last time.

161
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:56,240
The client insists on having you handle it.
Take another look.

162
00:15:56,240 --> 00:15:59,436
I said before, I won't take criminal cases.

163
00:16:02,060 --> 00:16:04,040
It's been years.

164
00:16:04,040 --> 00:16:07,880
Something can't be changed by time.

165
00:16:11,980 --> 00:16:13,580
Okay.

166
00:16:27,959 --> 00:16:31,400
<i>Hello, Ms. Wen Xiang.
Your new novel "Whisper in Your Ear"</i>

167
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:34,100
topped major lists as soon as it was serialized.

168
00:16:34,100 --> 00:16:37,400
<i>I hear that film companies are contacting you for the copyright.</i>

169
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:41,536
Could you give us a sneak peek?

170
00:16:41,536 --> 00:16:45,239
<i>First of all, thank you for supporting this novel.</i>

171
00:16:45,239 --> 00:16:49,320
It's about mutual unrequited love in high school.

172
00:16:49,320 --> 00:16:51,860
I really hope you'll all like it.

173
00:16:51,860 --> 00:16:54,240
As for the copyright,

174
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:57,160
I'll share with you once it's confirmed.

175
00:16:57,160 --> 00:16:59,773
Look. She's suspected of plagiarism.

176
00:16:59,773 --> 00:17:01,680
It seems true.

177
00:17:01,680 --> 00:17:04,259
Look at this comparison chart.

178
00:17:04,259 --> 00:17:05,728
Check it out. She plagiarized.

179
00:17:05,728 --> 00:17:07,919
- Yes, I agree.
- This...

180
00:17:07,919 --> 00:17:11,280
- Thank you.
- Ms. Wen Xiang, have you noticed

181
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:15,080
the controversy online
regarding your work's originality?

182
00:17:15,080 --> 00:17:18,179
In "New Year's Eve Fireworks", the plot, the dialogue,
<i>[Wen Xiang's novel is accused of plagiarism]</i>

183
00:17:18,179 --> 00:17:21,839
and even the male lead's monologue
largely overlap those by Poet.

184
00:17:21,839 --> 00:17:24,540
What caused such high similarity?

185
00:17:24,540 --> 00:17:28,060
Are the copyright buyers aware of this?

186
00:17:28,060 --> 00:17:33,580
Does this explain your previous high productivity?

187
00:17:33,580 --> 00:17:36,150
What do you think of
the current controversy online?

188
00:17:36,150 --> 00:17:39,872
Everyone. Like you, I just got the news.

189
00:17:39,872 --> 00:17:41,720
I hope you can give me some time.

190
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:45,660
I will definitely give everyone
and my work an explanation soon.

191
00:17:45,660 --> 00:17:47,560
Thank you.

192
00:17:47,560 --> 00:17:50,339
Ms. Wen Xiang! So you deny the plagiarism?

193
00:17:50,339 --> 00:17:52,380
- Yes, Ms. Wen Xiang, say something.
- Ms. Wen Xiang!

194
00:17:52,380 --> 00:17:54,400
- Ms. Wen Xiang!
- Wait! Ms. Wen Xiang!

195
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:56,480
- Please wait!
- Ms. Wen Xiang! We want a direct answer.

196
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:58,699
- Please reply. Ms. Wen Xiang!
- Ms. Wen Xiang!

197
00:17:58,699 --> 00:18:00,399
- Please wait, Ms. Wen Xiang!
- Ms. Wen Xiang!

198
00:18:00,399 --> 00:18:01,860
- For your six years of original creation...
- Ms. Wen Xiang!

199
00:18:01,860 --> 00:18:03,540
Ming Ying, what's going on?

200
00:18:03,540 --> 00:18:08,680
Your novel resembles "Her Smiling Eyes"
in so many tropes.

201
00:18:08,680 --> 00:18:10,340
- Ms. Wen Xiang!
- Are you leaving because you feel guilty?

202
00:18:10,340 --> 00:18:12,460
It's been six years. Why now?

203
00:18:12,460 --> 00:18:14,440
- Ms. Wen Xiang!
- Ms. Wen Xiang!

204
00:18:14,440 --> 00:18:16,419
- Please answer us.
- We want a direct reply.

205
00:18:16,419 --> 00:18:18,100
Please, Ms. Wen Xiang.

206
00:18:18,100 --> 00:18:19,839
Ms. Wen Xiang, say something!

207
00:18:19,839 --> 00:18:22,020
Ms. Wen Xiang! Ms. Wen Xiang!

208
00:18:22,020 --> 00:18:23,920
Ms. Wen Xiang!

209
00:18:26,260 --> 00:18:28,460
Check the comparison chart.

210
00:18:38,219 --> 00:18:41,900
It was published weeks before
"Whisper in Your Ear."

211
00:18:41,900 --> 00:18:47,480
The biggest difference is that yours centers on the heroine,
his centers on the hero.

212
00:18:48,300 --> 00:18:49,939
<i>Sorry. I took the wrong hand.</i>

213
00:18:49,939 --> 00:18:52,679
<i>No one knew that "I took the wrong hand"
was just a cover-up.</i>

214
00:18:52,679 --> 00:18:54,520
<i>"I Really Want to Whisper in Your Ear".</i>

215
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:56,879
<i>Just kidding. I didn't take the wrong hand.</i>

216
00:18:56,879 --> 00:18:58,939
<i>"Her Smiling Eyes."</i>

217
00:18:58,939 --> 00:19:02,140
Even the male lead's inner monologue is the same.

218
00:19:13,900 --> 00:19:17,780
I found it. The author's Weibo account.

219
00:19:17,780 --> 00:19:20,160
"Going back to school again."
<i>[A Poet]</i>

220
00:19:20,160 --> 00:19:22,020
A student?

221
00:19:22,020 --> 00:19:23,720
I'll message her to ask about it.

222
00:19:23,720 --> 00:19:27,076
Ask her why they are so similar.

223
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:32,000
<i>"Whisper in Your Ear" is my original work.</i>

224
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,780
<i> I can prove it.</i>

225
00:19:33,780 --> 00:19:39,220
<i>Yet I'm surprised and confused by the similarities.</i>

226
00:19:39,220 --> 00:19:43,400
<i>I'm writing to inquire about this.
I look forward to your reply.</i>

227
00:19:44,860 --> 00:19:47,720
Ten years ago, you endured unrequited love
because of him.

228
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:52,760
Ten years later, you based a fiction on this,
only to be accused of plagiarism.

229
00:19:52,760 --> 00:19:55,326
It's not a fiction.

230
00:19:57,980 --> 00:20:00,060
Alright.

231
00:20:00,060 --> 00:20:04,580
If I have to admit it, then I guess it is.

232
00:20:11,520 --> 00:20:16,380
A'Yu, the young man I mentioned yesterday
is available tomorrow.

233
00:20:16,380 --> 00:20:19,840
I'll show you his photos, okay? If you agree...

234
00:20:19,840 --> 00:20:22,180
Mom, I'm busy right now.

235
00:20:22,180 --> 00:20:25,160
Busy, busy, busy, all year round.
When are you not busy?

236
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:27,480
Dating and work don't conflict.

237
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:31,660
Mrs. Li said he's very capable.

238
00:20:31,660 --> 00:20:35,444
<i>Most notably, he's a lawyer.
I'll send you his photos first.</i>

239
00:20:35,444 --> 00:20:38,880
If he looks okay, go see him tomorrow.
I think he's quite nice.

240
00:20:38,880 --> 00:20:40,419
Okay.

241
00:20:48,020 --> 00:20:49,620
Hello.

242
00:20:50,420 --> 00:20:53,380
I'm Liu Mao from Zhikun Law Firm.

243
00:20:53,380 --> 00:20:55,620
Here's my business card.

244
00:20:55,620 --> 00:20:58,319
Hello. I'm Ruan Yu.

245
00:20:58,319 --> 00:20:59,540
Hello, hello.

246
00:20:59,540 --> 00:21:02,500
Mr. Liu, you seem much older than me.
[Liu Mao]

247
00:21:02,500 --> 00:21:06,090
You're a law firm partner at such a young age.

248
00:21:06,090 --> 00:21:08,260
A true "young talent".

249
00:21:08,260 --> 00:21:10,900
No, no. You flatter me.

250
00:21:10,900 --> 00:21:13,820
Our firm has four partners.

251
00:21:13,820 --> 00:21:17,620
I'm the doer, not very high-ranking.

252
00:21:17,620 --> 00:21:22,700
A senior counsel who lives abroad long-term
is more powerful.

253
00:21:22,700 --> 00:21:26,157
Living abroad means he's not a doer?

254
00:21:26,157 --> 00:21:28,260
No. That's not what I mean.

255
00:21:28,260 --> 00:21:30,700
I mean, he practices law abroad.

256
00:21:30,700 --> 00:21:34,740
You know, financial support is part of the work.

257
00:21:38,550 --> 00:21:40,520
<i>[Huai Song]</i>

258
00:21:40,520 --> 00:21:43,220
<i>This guy has sharp ears.</i>

259
00:21:45,052 --> 00:21:48,140
Excuse me, Ms. Ruan.
I don't talk about work in my personal life.

260
00:21:48,140 --> 00:21:49,780
It's okay to talk about work.

261
00:21:49,780 --> 00:21:54,284
No, really. I separate work from life.

262
00:21:54,900 --> 00:21:58,659
I mean, we can talk about work.

263
00:22:08,080 --> 00:22:11,519
Mr. Liu, sorry for bringing up work at lunch.

264
00:22:11,519 --> 00:22:12,759
It's okay.

265
00:22:12,759 --> 00:22:18,680
I'm used to drawing experience from life
and applying it to my work.

266
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:23,800
As they say, work is a part of life,
and life is a part of work.

267
00:22:25,859 --> 00:22:30,420
So, Mr. Liu, do you have any solutions?

268
00:22:31,452 --> 00:22:37,080
Based on your description,
she published online earlier than you did.

269
00:22:37,080 --> 00:22:40,566
In theory, she didn't plagiarize you.

270
00:22:40,566 --> 00:22:46,080
And as you said, so far,
she has neither shown up nor taken a stance.

271
00:22:46,080 --> 00:22:49,220
So she can't be considered a defendant.

272
00:22:49,220 --> 00:22:52,740
We can't sue everyone commenting online, right?

273
00:22:52,740 --> 00:22:56,540
Of course, it is feasible.

274
00:22:56,540 --> 00:22:58,580
But I wouldn't recommend it.

275
00:22:58,580 --> 00:23:01,860
Because it's thankless and unpromising.

276
00:23:01,860 --> 00:23:03,860
I see.

277
00:23:03,860 --> 00:23:07,860
Mr. Liu, could you give me some advice?

278
00:23:07,860 --> 00:23:12,440
Let the bullets fly for a while
and see what she wants.

279
00:23:16,880 --> 00:23:19,220
Excuse me.

280
00:23:19,220 --> 00:23:22,100
Uh, Mr. Liu, I have to go now.

281
00:23:22,100 --> 00:23:25,720
Thank you so much for your advice today.
Let's meet some other day.

282
00:23:26,880 --> 00:23:29,500
I've settled the bill.
Consider it the consultation fee.

283
00:23:29,500 --> 00:23:31,280
I'll transfer more if it's not enough.

284
00:23:31,280 --> 00:23:33,940
So kind of you. When will we meet again?

285
00:23:33,940 --> 00:23:36,200
When we find the defendant.

286
00:23:37,140 --> 00:23:40,700
He told me to wait and see until A Poet shows up.

287
00:23:40,700 --> 00:23:42,620
<i>Is he reliable?</i>

288
00:23:42,620 --> 00:23:43,910
I don't know.

289
00:23:43,910 --> 00:23:50,160
But I agree with him that
A Poet's stance matters to us.

290
00:23:50,160 --> 00:23:52,700
What if she clarifies that I didn't plagiarize.

291
00:23:52,700 --> 00:23:55,080
Theoretically,
you're lucky if she doesn't sue you.

292
00:23:55,080 --> 00:23:58,184
You really expect her to clarify?

293
00:23:58,800 --> 00:24:02,179
At least I'll try to convince her
it's my original work.

294
00:24:02,179 --> 00:24:04,919
<i>- I'll wait...</i>
- Wait!

295
00:24:04,919 --> 00:24:07,600
A Poet posted on Weibo.

296
00:24:10,919 --> 00:24:13,799
She's too much. A writer?

297
00:24:13,799 --> 00:24:15,820
So spineless!

298
00:24:15,820 --> 00:24:17,540
Which writer?

299
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:24,080
<i>I didn't plagiarize or mix tropes.
As for the similarities</i>

300
00:24:24,080 --> 00:24:27,239
<i>between "Whisper in Your Ear" and "Her Smiling Eyes",</i>

301
00:24:27,239 --> 00:24:31,320
<i>I've contacted the author to inquire
and I'm waiting for a reply.</i>

302
00:24:31,320 --> 00:24:35,140
<i>Once clear, I'll provide further explanation.</i>

303
00:24:35,140 --> 00:24:40,740
<i>God knows, this unrequited love
was my personal experience in high school.</i>

304
00:24:40,740 --> 00:24:43,060
Personal experience?

305
00:24:43,060 --> 00:24:47,339
She's a better actress than the pros.
See whose personal experience it is.

306
00:24:49,900 --> 00:24:54,146
<i>So heavy.
[Two months ago, Su City]</i>

307
00:25:06,460 --> 00:25:08,593
<i>My brother's old phone?</i>

308
00:25:22,593 --> 00:25:24,979
<i>The fireworks are beautiful tonight.</i>

309
00:25:24,979 --> 00:25:26,880
<i>And...</i>

310
00:25:26,880 --> 00:25:30,260
<i>Just kidding. I didn't take the wrong hand.</i>

311
00:25:30,260 --> 00:25:32,100
<i>Happy New Year.</i>

312
00:25:38,060 --> 00:25:40,219
<i>Oh my god.</i>

313
00:25:41,920 --> 00:25:43,896
<i>So much stuff.</i>

314
00:25:43,896 --> 00:25:47,660
So you found your brother's crush on a girl
from his old phone

315
00:25:47,660 --> 00:25:51,760
when you helped your grandma move?

316
00:25:51,760 --> 00:25:54,193
Keep it down!

317
00:25:56,260 --> 00:25:58,284
His crush.

318
00:25:59,020 --> 00:26:03,500
- So, this is your brother's experience?
- Yes.

319
00:26:03,500 --> 00:26:08,940
And that is Wen Xiang's experience.
They're both in the story.

320
00:26:09,733 --> 00:26:12,266
Is it possible that...

321
00:26:15,620 --> 00:26:17,800
What?

322
00:26:17,800 --> 00:26:20,140
You mean...

323
00:26:20,140 --> 00:26:23,280
Wen Xiang was my brother's schoolmate,

324
00:26:24,220 --> 00:26:28,320
he had a crush on her,
and she had a crush on him too?

325
00:26:28,320 --> 00:26:30,780
No way! That's impossible.

326
00:26:30,780 --> 00:26:32,400
Impossible.

327
00:26:33,640 --> 00:26:35,340
I'm viewing her Weibo.

328
00:26:35,340 --> 00:26:39,740
Look, she posted photos of Su cuisine.

329
00:26:39,740 --> 00:26:42,400
She's likely from here.

330
00:26:43,340 --> 00:26:46,264
It seems so.

331
00:26:47,780 --> 00:26:50,620
It can't be that coincidental, can it?

332
00:26:54,540 --> 00:26:56,473
Impressive, Zhao Yi!

333
00:26:56,473 --> 00:27:00,700
You aren't good at studying,

334
00:27:00,700 --> 00:27:03,144
but still have a sharp mind.

335
00:27:04,670 --> 00:27:06,573
Thanks.

336
00:27:17,300 --> 00:27:18,820
Zhao Yi,

337
00:27:18,820 --> 00:27:23,759
your hairstyle is so cool today.

338
00:27:23,759 --> 00:27:27,659
And your skin is looking amazing.

339
00:27:27,659 --> 00:27:33,200
And your outfit, though the same as usual,
is extremely handsome today.

340
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:37,379
Look, a chiseled jawline, and an amazing profile.

341
00:27:37,379 --> 00:27:43,399
Incredible!
Even a school hunk looks small by your side...

342
00:27:43,399 --> 00:27:45,193
That's enough.

343
00:27:45,193 --> 00:27:48,340
Flattery out of the blue
means you're up to no good.

344
00:27:48,340 --> 00:27:50,910
We're great buddies, aren't we?

345
00:27:51,640 --> 00:27:54,600
That depends on what you're going to say next.

346
00:27:54,600 --> 00:27:57,459
Considering your wide network,

347
00:27:57,459 --> 00:28:02,559
go look into Wen Xiang for me.

348
00:28:05,739 --> 00:28:08,766
I just knew you're my buddy!

349
00:28:08,766 --> 00:28:10,060
What do you know?

350
00:28:10,060 --> 00:28:12,500
It means three months of math homework.

351
00:28:19,820 --> 00:28:21,820
One month will do.

352
00:28:26,300 --> 00:28:27,800
Deal!

353
00:28:27,800 --> 00:28:29,940
A cup of milk tea.

354
00:28:34,870 --> 00:28:36,610
<i>[Prince Cafe]</i>

355
00:28:41,580 --> 00:28:44,800
Okay, okay.

356
00:28:45,540 --> 00:28:48,780
Thanks. I'll treat you to crayfish next time.

357
00:28:48,780 --> 00:28:51,170
What? What did he say?

358
00:28:59,980 --> 00:29:01,233
<i>[Ruan Yu]</i>

359
00:29:02,220 --> 00:29:04,560
Ruan Yu?

360
00:29:05,580 --> 00:29:08,081
She's the one you're looking for.

361
00:29:11,520 --> 00:29:14,780
<i>[Wen Xiang]</i>

362
00:29:17,620 --> 00:29:23,560
Zhao, go the whole way
and follow me to the school art gallery.

363
00:29:23,560 --> 00:29:25,260
What for?

364
00:29:26,240 --> 00:29:28,700
To confirm something.

365
00:29:40,939 --> 00:29:43,179
It should be here.

366
00:29:43,179 --> 00:29:45,000
The piano.

367
00:29:45,879 --> 00:29:47,580
Zhao, come here!

368
00:29:47,580 --> 00:29:49,606
Help me move this.

369
00:29:49,606 --> 00:29:53,600
Do you think the wall has been repainted?

370
00:29:53,600 --> 00:29:57,439
I don't think so. They're stingy.

371
00:29:57,439 --> 00:29:59,000
Let me do it.

372
00:30:03,780 --> 00:30:09,900
In Wen Xiang's novel,
the heroine wrote some initials

373
00:30:09,900 --> 00:30:14,680
on the wall of the piano room
where the hero practices.

374
00:30:16,979 --> 00:30:18,300
What are you looking for?

375
00:30:18,300 --> 00:30:20,220
Let me help you.

376
00:30:23,880 --> 00:30:27,666
[RYXHXHS]

377
00:30:29,040 --> 00:30:31,000
I found it!

378
00:30:34,156 --> 00:30:39,320
RYXHXHS...

379
00:30:39,320 --> 00:30:43,456
Loves Xu Huai Song?

380
00:30:44,380 --> 00:30:47,116
Who's RY? Tell me.

381
00:30:47,116 --> 00:30:49,880
Is it Ren Yi from Class 1, or Ran Yu from Class 5?

382
00:30:49,880 --> 00:30:51,660
Nanny Rong from Grade 10?

383
00:30:51,660 --> 00:30:54,779
Xu Huai Shi, you're dating a junior at this age!

384
00:30:54,779 --> 00:30:59,520
Ruan Yu loves Xu Huai Song.

385
00:31:00,300 --> 00:31:01,820
My god!

386
00:31:01,820 --> 00:31:04,928
Zhao Yi, this is so touching!

387
00:31:04,928 --> 00:31:07,640
Hey, what are you two doing?
Which class are you in?

388
00:31:07,640 --> 00:31:09,340
Get out here!

389
00:31:12,900 --> 00:31:15,740
Your IQ is touching, too.

390
00:31:30,660 --> 00:31:33,580
You stayed up all night?

391
00:31:35,140 --> 00:31:37,259
Strange.

392
00:31:37,259 --> 00:31:39,780
That's more than similar.

393
00:31:39,780 --> 00:31:42,739
Remember? In my novel,

394
00:31:42,739 --> 00:31:46,700
potted plants were popular at school.

395
00:31:46,700 --> 00:31:49,910
When others grow clover and mimosa,

396
00:31:49,910 --> 00:31:52,639
I refit mine with other seeds. Remember?

397
00:31:52,639 --> 00:31:53,920
Yeah.

398
00:31:53,920 --> 00:31:57,977
- You grew sunflowers and lavender at the same time.
- Yes.

399
00:31:57,977 --> 00:32:00,420
An early pastoral heroine.

400
00:32:00,420 --> 00:32:02,780
Come and see.

401
00:32:02,780 --> 00:32:05,700
See what A Poet wrote here.

402
00:32:05,700 --> 00:32:07,932
- Hurry, come here.
- What? What did you find?

403
00:32:07,932 --> 00:32:09,020
Look at this.

404
00:32:09,020 --> 00:32:12,020
"That weekend, she left school
with her Little Florist,

405
00:32:12,020 --> 00:32:14,717
where sunflower and lavender bloomed."

406
00:32:14,717 --> 00:32:17,760
- This is way too similar! Goodness!
- Yeah.

407
00:32:17,760 --> 00:32:20,120
Who on earth is it?

408
00:32:20,120 --> 00:32:23,399
If no progress is made by 9:00 p.m.,

409
00:32:23,399 --> 00:32:26,739
your novel will be removed. Look at the time!

410
00:32:32,700 --> 00:32:36,223
<i>Hello. Sorry for the trouble.</i>

411
00:32:36,223 --> 00:32:39,900
<i>"Her Smiling Eyes" isn't my original,</i>

412
00:32:39,900 --> 00:32:43,059
<i>but adapted from an outline my friend bought.</i>

413
00:32:43,059 --> 00:32:45,820
<i>Sorry for violating your rights.</i>

414
00:32:45,820 --> 00:32:49,519
<i>I'm willing to publicly explain this
and apologize to you,</i>

415
00:32:49,519 --> 00:32:52,639
<i>delete my article, and close my account.</i>

416
00:32:52,639 --> 00:32:57,479
<i>I drafted a statement, attached for your review.</i>

417
00:32:57,479 --> 00:32:59,879
An outline leak?

418
00:32:59,879 --> 00:33:02,580
Who else did you show the outline to?

419
00:33:02,580 --> 00:33:04,560
No one.

420
00:33:06,180 --> 00:33:07,459
My USB flash disk!

421
00:33:07,459 --> 00:33:10,899
I brought it to the cafe
where we discussed the outline.

422
00:33:10,899 --> 00:33:13,060
Was it left there?

423
00:33:19,940 --> 00:33:21,920
<i>What's going on?</i>

424
00:33:21,920 --> 00:33:25,059
<i>Your novel... is going to be a hit.</i>

425
00:33:25,059 --> 00:33:28,340
Yeah, she said the outline was purchased.

426
00:33:28,340 --> 00:33:29,939
Wait. Where are you going?

427
00:33:29,939 --> 00:33:32,959
The cafe, Ming Ying. You should go home.

428
00:33:32,959 --> 00:33:35,920
- Okay, and...
- I know. I'll ask her about the source.

429
00:33:35,920 --> 00:33:37,476
Yes.

430
00:33:38,720 --> 00:33:41,593
Okay. Don't rush us. We're sure.

431
00:33:43,752 --> 00:33:46,020
Buddy, here you are.

432
00:33:46,020 --> 00:33:47,639
Thanks.

433
00:33:48,620 --> 00:33:51,060
She asked me about the source.

434
00:33:51,060 --> 00:33:53,240
What should I say?

435
00:33:53,240 --> 00:33:56,020
I told you it was a bad idea.

436
00:33:56,020 --> 00:33:58,700
Then tell her the truth.

437
00:33:58,700 --> 00:34:02,900
That's even worse.
If she knows, so will my brother.

438
00:34:02,900 --> 00:34:06,639
If he knows I wrote a novel based on his draft,

439
00:34:06,639 --> 00:34:08,920
I'm dead!

440
00:34:08,920 --> 00:34:10,884
He's a lawyer.

441
00:34:10,884 --> 00:34:14,097
He won't break the law.

442
00:34:14,097 --> 00:34:18,220
He'll cut off my allowance, which will kill me.

443
00:34:19,800 --> 00:34:21,539
That makes sense.

444
00:34:22,979 --> 00:34:25,860
Listen, tell her that

445
00:34:25,860 --> 00:34:29,580
you signed a non-disclosure agreement
with the seller.

446
00:34:29,580 --> 00:34:31,860
Anyway, she doesn't know you.

447
00:34:31,860 --> 00:34:36,900
But that would be unfair to Ruan Yu.

448
00:34:37,640 --> 00:34:43,019
Hey, is it possible
that my brother still loves Ruan Yu,

449
00:34:43,019 --> 00:34:46,244
and he'll reward me for what I did?

450
00:34:46,244 --> 00:34:50,020
Please! It has been ten years. Still?

451
00:34:50,020 --> 00:34:52,540
Do you think he'd love one person his whole life?

452
00:34:52,540 --> 00:34:56,819
- You don't understand men.
- Because I'm not, and I don't need to.

453
00:35:03,900 --> 00:35:06,852
<i>Please post the statement first.</i>

454
00:35:10,980 --> 00:35:14,380
<i>[Apology Statement]</i>

455
00:35:14,380 --> 00:35:18,020
No one in the cafe saw it.
We checked the security footage.

456
00:35:18,020 --> 00:35:20,780
But it's too small to be noticed.

457
00:35:20,780 --> 00:35:24,080
<i>Anyway, her statement put it to an end.</i>

458
00:35:24,080 --> 00:35:29,759
<i>After grocery shopping, I'll come over
and boil away your bad luck in hot pot.</i>

459
00:35:36,660 --> 00:35:45,786
<i>[Forwarded Apology Statement]</i>

460
00:35:50,099 --> 00:35:52,100
<i>It's a common tactic</i>

461
00:35:52,100 --> 00:35:54,980
<i>to plagiarize the ideas of unknown writers</i>

462
00:35:54,980 --> 00:35:57,386
<i>and pay in exchange for their silence.</i>

463
00:35:57,386 --> 00:36:01,720
<i>The fake statement... Wen Xiang is fooling us.</i>

464
00:36:01,720 --> 00:36:05,340
<i>The web novel community is corrupted
by people like her.</i>

465
00:36:05,340 --> 00:36:07,839
<i>Qianhe Net, do something!</i>

466
00:36:07,839 --> 00:36:12,060
<i>Only when Wen Xiang is banned
can emerging talents survive.</i>

467
00:36:12,060 --> 00:36:14,180
<i>Wen Xiang, quit the internet!</i>

468
00:36:16,439 --> 00:36:22,140
A Poet is a new account with few readers
and little exposure.

469
00:36:22,140 --> 00:36:27,380
Yet the news went viral, as if planned.

470
00:36:27,380 --> 00:36:31,940
It must be Su Cheng. She's cunning and vicious.

471
00:36:31,940 --> 00:36:35,100
Remember? When she signed with Qianhe Net,

472
00:36:35,100 --> 00:36:38,777
she blamed her poor work on an editor,

473
00:36:38,777 --> 00:36:42,960
and made the young girl lose her job.

474
00:36:42,960 --> 00:36:45,200
Watch out.

475
00:36:45,200 --> 00:36:48,324
Or you'll be another slaughtered lamb.

476
00:36:48,324 --> 00:36:51,833
If you don't act,

477
00:36:54,335 --> 00:36:57,468
you'll be cooked like this.

478
00:36:59,080 --> 00:37:02,846
Who told you I'll wait to be slaughtered?

479
00:37:02,846 --> 00:37:05,719
If we play dirty, we may not be her match.

480
00:37:05,719 --> 00:37:10,000
But if we play by rules, she may not be our match.

481
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:11,540
You have a plan?

482
00:37:11,540 --> 00:37:16,060
Look, the slanderers on the trending topics

483
00:37:16,060 --> 00:37:19,660
of Qianhe Net's Weibo and other platforms
must be her trolls.

484
00:37:19,660 --> 00:37:22,900
I can accuse her of defamation

485
00:37:22,900 --> 00:37:25,780
considering the large-scale
planned slander, right?

486
00:37:25,780 --> 00:37:28,896
Your blind date really inspired you.

487
00:37:29,520 --> 00:37:32,556
We have an appointment at his firm tomorrow.

488
00:37:32,556 --> 00:37:35,044
I hope it'll go well.

489
00:37:40,740 --> 00:37:46,980
<i>[Zhikun Law Firm]</i>

490
00:37:46,980 --> 00:37:49,417
Hello. I have an appointment
with Lawyer Liu, Liu Mao.

491
00:37:49,417 --> 00:37:52,119
Okay, I'll check for you.

492
00:38:03,380 --> 00:38:08,160
<i>[Monday, September 9, 2024]</i>

493
00:38:09,766 --> 00:38:13,420
<i>September 9, 2013, sunny.</i>

494
00:38:13,420 --> 00:38:17,064
After today,
I'll remember Xu Huai Song for many years.

495
00:38:17,064 --> 00:38:21,440
<i>We think effort shouldn't be denied by a doomed failure.</i>

496
00:38:21,440 --> 00:38:27,659
<i>Success and failure
are deeply rooted in our subconscious.</i>

497
00:38:29,540 --> 00:38:35,380
<i>Facing an insurmountable barrier
or inevitable abyss,</i>

498
00:38:35,380 --> 00:38:41,119
<i>perhaps they are the ones struggling,
just like you.</i>

499
00:38:41,119 --> 00:38:45,880
<i>So we think only when we give up</i>

500
00:38:45,880 --> 00:38:50,900
<i>can we quit the painful cycle
and find hope elsewhere.</i>

501
00:39:29,420 --> 00:39:33,860
<i>Instead of repeating
the painful cycle of failure and expectation,</i>

502
00:39:33,860 --> 00:39:39,180
<i>it's better to turn around and take another route</i>

503
00:39:39,180 --> 00:39:44,420
<i>where new hope and life lie ahead.</i>

504
00:39:44,420 --> 00:39:47,106
<i>[Debate Final, Su City No.1 High School, 2013]</i>

505
00:39:50,139 --> 00:39:54,860
<i>Opposition, congratulations on your win.</i>

506
00:39:58,660 --> 00:40:03,880
<i>The Best Debater award goes to Xu Huai Song.</i>

507
00:40:10,300 --> 00:40:11,619
<i>Congratulations.</i>

508
00:40:11,619 --> 00:40:13,740
<i>Thank you, Principal.</i>

509
00:40:13,740 --> 00:40:19,040
<i>Huai Song, without a preset side,
which opinion would you support?</i>

510
00:40:19,040 --> 00:40:21,200
<i>We'd like to hear from you.</i>

511
00:40:24,500 --> 00:40:28,459
<i>A line from a movie can represent my choice,</i>

512
00:40:28,459 --> 00:40:34,260
<i>"I'll keep searching,
even if the endless stars blur my hope,</i>

513
00:40:34,260 --> 00:40:37,800
<i>even if alone."</i>

514
00:40:39,020 --> 00:40:40,499
Ruan Yu?

515
00:40:40,499 --> 00:40:41,780
Lawyer Liu.

516
00:40:41,780 --> 00:40:44,140
Excuse me for coming late.

517
00:40:44,140 --> 00:40:46,140
It's fine. I was early.

518
00:40:46,140 --> 00:40:48,820
- Let's go to the meeting room.
- Okay.

519
00:40:49,612 --> 00:40:51,300
This way.

520
00:40:51,300 --> 00:40:53,980
By the way, Ruan Yu, our legal counsel,

521
00:40:53,980 --> 00:40:57,360
the one I mentioned last time,
might join us today.

522
00:40:57,360 --> 00:40:59,079
He returned recently.

523
00:40:59,079 --> 00:41:01,919
He's interested in your case
and wants to get involved.

524
00:41:01,919 --> 00:41:03,740
Would you mind?

525
00:41:03,740 --> 00:41:07,620
I don't mind. More lawyers, more hope.

526
00:41:07,620 --> 00:41:10,859
Technically, he hasn't passed the bar exam here,

527
00:41:10,859 --> 00:41:13,980
so he can't be called a lawyer in China.

528
00:41:13,980 --> 00:41:15,540
If you mind, I can tell him.

529
00:41:15,540 --> 00:41:17,780
It's really okay.

530
00:41:17,780 --> 00:41:23,780
Despite a lack of qualification,
he still wants to get involved.

531
00:41:23,780 --> 00:41:27,820
Is the big shot here to supervise you?

532
00:41:29,120 --> 00:41:32,020
Well, you might be right.

533
00:41:32,020 --> 00:41:34,000
Life is tough.

534
00:41:35,459 --> 00:41:36,939
This way, Ms. Ruan.

535
00:41:36,939 --> 00:41:39,239
- Please come in.
- Thank you.

536
00:41:47,580 --> 00:41:49,620
Let me introduce you.

537
00:42:33,399 --> 00:42:35,860
<i>Xu Huai Song?</i>

538
00:42:35,860 --> 00:42:38,619
<i>How can it be Xu Huai Song?</i>

539
00:42:45,000 --> 00:42:55,010
team name

540
00:43:03,539 --> 00:43:06,280
<i>I'm looking forward to tonight.</i>

541
00:43:06,280 --> 00:43:07,780
<i>I heard there's a performance tonight.</i>

542
00:43:07,780 --> 00:43:09,440
<i>Here!</i>

543
00:43:11,904 --> 00:43:13,916
<i>So many people have come.</i>

544
00:43:14,740 --> 00:43:17,000
<i>So lively.</i>

545
00:43:18,380 --> 00:43:21,279
<i>Here, here, hurry!</i>

546
00:43:33,339 --> 00:43:35,239
<i>Coming!</i>

547
00:43:55,419 --> 00:44:00,260
<i>Ten, nine, eight, seven,</i>

548
00:44:00,260 --> 00:44:03,979
<i>six, five, four,</i>

549
00:44:03,979 --> 00:44:09,139
<i>three, two, one!</i>

550
00:44:32,410 --> 00:44:37,450
<i>'Yesterday' - Vision Wei</i>

